  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Blood supply to the sigmoid colon during open abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) repair is at
      risk. Ischemia of the sigmoid colon after AAA repair is potentially devastative. No reliable
      measures to prevent it are available and the underlying mechanisms are poorly understood. The
      aim of this study is to describe intraoperative perfusion patterns of the sigmoid colon
      during open AAA repair and their potential impact on postoperative outcome.
    </textblock>
